\ls2\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Now most separate this verse and the next and maybe even in your Bible they are separated by a header about.\'a0 \cf2 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 I believe they are incredibly connected and so Paul creates tension as to the fact that some will not finish the race they started out in Christ.\cf2 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 They will reveal they were never really saved and in doing so reveal who they really are.\'a0 \cf2 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 Because the next verse is what separates who is serous and who is not...it's what is most important\cf2 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cf5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec5 How you handle the next doesn't change anything...it just reveals something (I can say this better)\cf2 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 \
